'''Ihor Berezovskyi''' ({{lang-ua| <U+0406><U+0433><U+043E><U+0440> <U+041E><U+043B><U+0435><U+0433><U+043E><U+0432><U+0438><U+0447> <U+0411><U+0435><U+0440><U+0435><U+0437><U+043E><U+0432><U+0441><U+044C><U+043A><U+0438><U+0439>}}; born 24 August 1990 in [[Ukrainian SSR]]) is a [[professional]] [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[football (soccer)|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] who plays for [[FC Obolon Kyiv]] in the [[Ukrainian Premier League]].

Berezovskyi is product of youth team systems of Kirovohrad city. Made his debut for FC Obolon entering as a substituted player in game against [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk]] on 9 April 2011 in [[Ukrainian Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccer.ru|title=<U+0418><U+0433><U+043E><U+0440><U+044C> <U+0411><U+0435><U+0440><U+0435><U+0437><U+043E><U+0432><U+0441><U+043A><U+0438><U+0439>|url=http://www.soccer.ru/players/21316.shtml|language=Russian|date=2011-04-09}}</ref>

